**Legal Simplicity**
All photos on Pexels can be used for free.


*What is allowed?*
We tried to keep the Pexels License as simple as possible. Keep reading to find out more.

- All photos on Pexels are free to use.
- Attribution is not required. Giving credit to the photographer or Pexels is not necessary but always appreciated.
- You can modify the photos. Be creative and edit the photos as you like.


*What is not allowed?*
Respect the hard work of our contributors and keep these restrictions in mind.

x Identifiable people may not appear in a bad light or in a way that is offensive.
x Don't sell unaltered copies of a photo, e.g. don't sell it as a stock photo, poster, print or on a physical product without adding any value.
x Don't imply endorsement of your product by people or brands on the image.
x Don't redistribute or sell the photos on other stock photo or wallpaper platforms.